            "description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Powerful waves, driven by offshore storm surges, struck several areas in the Marshall Islands on Saturday, January 20. Local media reports indicate that the waves caused flooding, impacting two airports at Ailinglaplap Atoll. The airports remain closed due to rocks, coral, and debris, with repairs expected to take weeks. Additionally, the Army base experienced substantial damage from the massive waves.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">As per a brief update from the IFRC delegate deployed to the Sub Office in the North Pacific, this event originated from a powerful winter storm system in the far northern Pacific. The strong winds generated a large swell that reached Roi Namur Islet in the northern part of Kwajalein Atoll, affecting the US Military base.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">This weather-driven wave and inundation event, distinct from a tsunami, resulted from a significant wind-generated swell breaking on the Roi-Namur shores. Reports suggest inundation in other locations, including Arno Atoll and the runway in Ailinglapalap of Marshall Islands.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Limited and delayed ground reports hint at potential impacts on other islands and atolls. Coastal evacuations occurred in Kosrae of Federated States of Micronesia(FSM), with islands across the FSM experiencing inundation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"EN-US\">Findings from the assessment visit conducted on 23rd and 24th January 2024:&nbsp;</span></u></strong></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0mm;\" type=\"disc\">\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;Many houses are swept away by the ocean waves. The plinth of the house which was made from cement concrete has little or no damage while the superstructures that were made of plywood/wood and the Tin sheets have been completely damaged.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Rainwater harvesting was one of the sources of water for the households on the Arno Islands. As the water storage tanks and the houses are swept away, this resource is completely inaccessible.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The hand-dug open wells which was the second source of water on the island for families is filled with sand and salt water.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The boats which are the primary means to stay connected with the other nearby islands are also damaged.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The household items of the families such as the cooking utensils, clothes, and bedding are swept away by the waves.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The affected people are on the nearby Island in the public building</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"EN-US\">Short-term needs:</span></u></strong></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0mm;\" type=\"disc\">\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Food, shelter, household items</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Salvaging materials from the damaged houses</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Psychosocial support</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Cash assistance to meet the immediate needs of the families.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Community rainwater harvesting system to meet the water demand in the short-term.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
            "summary": "MHL: Storm Surge - 01-2024 - Marshall Islands: Winter Storm and Flood- 01-2024",
            "translation_module_original_language": "en"
          }
        ],
